comment: Moore (CHI) maintains legal guarding position and makes incidental contact with Jackson (DET) that does not affect his drive to the basket and shot attempt.
[Incidental or immaterial] Baynes (DET) extends his arms to Moore's (CHI) back.
Caldwell-Pope (DET) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Butler's (CHI) shot attempt.
Morris (DET) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Butler's (CHI) drive to the basket and shot attempt.
Butler (CHI) dislodges Morris (DET) after he obtains the rebound.
Jackson (DET) dislodges Dunleavy (CHI) prior to the inbound pass that affects his ability to defend the play.
Morris (DET) makes incidental contact with Butler (CHI) that does not affect his RSBQ.

After communicating with the Replay Center the ruling on the court that Butler (CHI) was in the RA when contact occurred with Jackson (DET) was upheld and a blocking foul assessed. The lifting of one's foot/heel does not remove a player from RA.
Butler (CHI) is in the restricted area when he defends Jackson's (DET) drive and shot attempt.
Caldwell-Pope (DET) makes incidental contact with Butler (CHI) that does not affect his RSBQ.
Gasol (CHI) commits a take foul on Jackson (DET).
